data.title: What’s an old comedy movie that still holds up well?
data.meta_description:
Answer (1 of 12): I’ve used this before for a different question. Black and white. 1938. A classic screwball comedy. Sounds grim for modern audiences. It isn’t. It is nearly lethally funny.
